$interpreted: Tingko: Princess, does your leg hurt? Maybe you should walk slower? This injury isn't like your sprain before—I saw blood this time.
Tindoiimu: It's already a lot better. Jihasaha was careful.
Jiyanama: Isn't the Peace Ceremony tomorrow? Tingko, why don't you and the princess go together?
Tingko: Eh? Can we?
Jiyanama: Why not? You've both been stuck in this house for days, it's making me antsy. Sometimes I need time alone, too.
Jiyanama: It's chilly outside. I've stitched a shawl for the princess. Don't forget to take it with you.
Tindoiimu: Jiyanama... for me...?
Jiyanama: And don't forget to take Jihasaha so he doesn't keep bothering me. That country boy has never seen the world.
Tingko: Looks like Jiyanama's getting back to normal!
Tindoiimu: Yeah... I hope so.
Tingko: She is. She's even worried about Jihasaha.
Tingko: But... it's surprising that she isn't going to the Peace Ceremony. She used to love going...
Tindoiimu: ...What happened to Faayida probably changed her mind.
Tingko: Well... what do you think? Do you wanna go?
Tindoiimu: ...I suppose so. Let's give Jiyanama a night off.
Tindoiimu: And I bet you'd love to spend some time with Jihasaha, right?
Tingko: Hey! Is it that obvious~?
Tingko: I'll go get him, then!!!
Tingko: Ooh it's so busy! Last time must have been 3 years ago, right? And this time it's in Feihua City~!
Jihasaha: So this is the Peace Ceremony...
Tindoiimu: (Kind of reminds me of that circus performance...)
Qilin Guard: Hey, slow down! Stay where we can see you! If you're up to something, then next time your princess won't be allowed outside!
Jihasaha: You want to say that again, buddy?
Tindoiimu: ...It's fine. We'll just walk slower. We're here to see the ceremony—Don't let people like that bring us down.
Excited Citizen: Ho boy! Ho boy! The dance is starting!
Excited Citizen: The best part of the ceremony is always the shamans ~~ I've been waiting forever! So excited!!
Lively Citizen: The water shaman is definitely gonna be Miss Soohyeon, right!?
Excited Citizen: Duh! She's the best dancer in the east! I've run to three different cities just to watch her dance!
Lively Citizen: She's got beautiful dance moves for sure, but she's engaged! Me~ I've got my eye on Chiyuki~
Lively Citizen: It's a shame she's not attending the ceremony...
Tingko: Did you hear that? The dance is about to start! Let's go!
Tindoiimu: Tingko, calm down—
Jihasaha: Wait...
Qilin Guard: Stop! I told you not to run! We wanna see Miss Soohyeon's dance too, dammit!
Tindoiimu: Did we miss it?
Tingko: No. It's just starting~
Tindoiimu: (That person... isn't looking at the stage?)
Tindoiimu: (Are they looking at the crowd? I can't see too clearly, but... it looks like a member of the Insect Tribe?)
Jihasaha: ...You also noticed?
Tindoiimu: Yes.
Jihasaha: I can't be sure, but if it really is a member of our tribe, and they're planning something here...
Tindoiimu: He's trying to escape. Get him!
Tingko: Princess? Jihasaha? Where are you going? I want to—
Tindoiimu: Should we be leaving Tingko alone?
Jihasaha: It'd be too dangerous for her here. Relax—Tingko will be fine.
Tindoiimu: Yeah...
???: Who are you? Why are you sticking your nose in our business?
Tindoiimu: ...My name is Tindoiimu. I don't know what you're planning, but as princess of the Insect Tribe, I order you to stop!
Tindoiimu: If someone from our tribe ruins the East Alliance's Peace Ceremony, then our already strained relationship will—
???: Insect Tribe?
???: We are servants of the almighty Sdorica. We have no affiliation with you bugs!
Tindoiimu: You're not from the Insect Tribe!?
???: It appears... they're humans from the west!?
???: It doesn't matter who we are—you're both about to die here! You won't interfere!
Tindoiimu: After them!
Jihasaha: Dammit, they're gone!
Jihasaha: ...Was that an explosion!?
Tindoiimu: Let's go!
